sys_hub_action_type_definition.description:
Creates a firewall for ingress rule in the specified project.

Inputs:

  • Project ID - Unique ID of the project.
  • Name - Name of the resource.
  • Network - Name of the network.
  • Allowed - Allowed is an object containing IP Protocal,Ports.
  • Denied - Denied is an object containing IP Protocal,Ports.
  • Description - An optional description of this resource.
  • Priority - Priority for this rule.
  • Source Ranges - Firewall rule applies only to traffic that has a source IP address in these ranges.
  • Source Tags - Firewall rule applies only to traffic with source IPs that match the primary network interfaces of VM instances that have the tag and are in the same VPC network.
  • Source Service Accounts - Firewall rules apply only to traffic originating from an instance with a service account in this list..
  • Log Config Enable - This field denotes whether to enable logging for a particular firewall rule.
  • Disabled Denotes whether the firewall rule is disabled.

Outputs:

  • Firewall - Firewall is an object containing Name,ID,Operation Type,Target Link,Target ID,Status,User,Progress,Insert Time,Start Time,Self Link,Kind.
  • Status - If the request is executed successfully, Status is set to “Success”. If there is a failure in Google Virtual Private Network, Status is set to “Error".
  • Error Message - Reason for error. Populated only when an error occurs.

Error Messages:

  • Invalid Project ID has been passed.
  • Requested network is doesn't exist.
  • Requested firewall name is already created.
  • Invalid IP protocol specification has been passed.
  • Invalid port range specification has been passed.
  • Service accounts must be valid RFC 822 email addresses.
  • Should not specify both allowed and denied in the same time.
  • Invalid authorization header. The access token you're using is either expired or invalid.

To use this action, a corresponding Google Virtual Private Cloud connection and credential must be created and associated with the Google Virtual Private Cloud Connection & Credential alias. Learn More

Note: Requires a subscription for production use. Read More.

sys_hub_action_type_snapshot.description:
Creates a firewall for ingress rule in the specified project.

Inputs:

  • Project ID - Unique ID of the project.
  • Name - Name of the resource.
  • Network - Name of the network.
  • Allowed - Allowed is an object containing IP Protocal,Ports.
  • Denied - Denied is an object containing IP Protocal,Ports.
  • Description - An optional description of this resource.
  • Priority - Priority for this rule.
  • Source Ranges - Firewall rule applies only to traffic that has a source IP address in these ranges.
  • Source Tags - Firewall rule applies only to traffic with source IPs that match the primary network interfaces of VM instances that have the tag and are in the same VPC network.
  • Source Service Accounts - Firewall rules apply only to traffic originating from an instance with a service account in this list..
  • Log Config Enable - This field denotes whether to enable logging for a particular firewall rule.
  • Disabled Denotes whether the firewall rule is disabled.

Outputs:

  • Firewall - Firewall is an object containing Name,ID,Operation Type,Target Link,Target ID,Status,User,Progress,Insert Time,Start Time,Self Link,Kind.
  • Status - If the request is executed successfully, Status is set to “Success”. If there is a failure in Google Virtual Private Network, Status is set to “Error".
  • Error Message - Reason for error. Populated only when an error occurs.

Error Messages:

  • Invalid Project ID has been passed.
  • Requested network is doesn't exist.
  • Requested firewall name is already created.
  • Invalid IP protocol specification has been passed.
  • Invalid port range specification has been passed.
  • Service accounts must be valid RFC 822 email addresses.
  • Should not specify both allowed and denied in the same time.
  • Invalid authorization header. The access token you're using is either expired or invalid.

To use this action, a corresponding Google Virtual Private Cloud connection and credential must be created and associated with the Google Virtual Private Cloud Connection & Credential alias. Learn More

Note: Requires a subscription for production use. Read More.
